<!-- SC_OFF --><div class="md"><p>In the 10th, 72nd and 82nd line in <code>/var/log/archinstall/install.log</code> there is my encryption password in plain text, and the file has the following permissions: <code>-rw-r--r--</code>, which means every user can read it, so beware.</p> <p>I think I installed Arch in february.</p> <p>It seems like someone reported a similar concern on Github: <a href="https://github.com/archlinux/archinstall/issues/1111">https://github.com/archlinux/archinstall/issues/1111</a></p> </div><!-- SC_ON --> &#32; submitted by &#32; <a href="https://www.reddit.com/user/peliblando"> /u/peliblando </a> <br/> <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wemldw/why_the_hell_did_archinstall_save_my_encryption/">[link]</a></span> &#32; <span><a href="https://www.reddit.com/r/archlinux/comments/wemldw/why_the_hell_did_archinstall_save_my_encryption/">[comments]</a></span>